28  \details
29 
30  This [omdl] formatted data table has been assembled using a script
31  that converts the polyhedra data obtained from [Anthony Thyssen]'s
32  [Studies into Polyhedra]. The vertices are tabulated in both their
33  original Cartesian as well as their converted spherical coordinate
34  form, which is convenient when scaling. The data originates from
35  one of three sources:
36 
37  \li Exact Mathematics as presented by [Anthony Thyssen],
38  \li the [Polyhedron Database] maintained by [Netlib], and
39  \li an [Encyclopedia of Polyhedra] by [George W. Hart].
40 
41  [omdl]: https://github.com/royasutton/omdl
42 
43  [Anthony Thyssen]: http://www.ict.griffith.edu.au/anthony/anthony.html
44  [Studies into Polyhedra]: http://www.ict.griffith.edu.au/anthony/graphics/polyhedra
45 
46  [George W. Hart]: http://www.georgehart.com
47  [Encyclopedia of Polyhedra]: http://www.georgehart.com/virtual-polyhedra/vp.html
48 
49  [Netlib]: http://www.netlib.org
50  [Polyhedron Database]: http://www.netlib.org/polyhedra
51 
52  \amu_pathid parent (++path_parent)
53  \amu_pathid group (++path)
54 
55  \ingroup \amu_eval(${group})
56 *******************************************************************************/
57 
58 //----------------------------------------------------------------------------//
59 /***************************************************************************//**
60  \addtogroup \amu_eval(${parent})
61  @{
62 
63  \defgroup \amu_eval(${group}) Polyhedra
64  \brief Tables of polyhedra vertices, faces, and edges.
65 
66  \details
67 
68  Database of polyhedra vertices, faces, and edges. Classes of
69  polyhedra are grouped into separate files. The file
70  polyhedra_all.scad contains all polyhedra from all files. Each
71  table uses the following column data structure.
72 
73  | field | description |
74  |:-----:|:--------------------|
75  | id | identifier |
76  | n | name |
77  | o | other name |
78  | g | group |
79  | d | data source |
80  | c | cartesian vertices |
81  | s | spherical vertices |
82  | f | faces |
83  | e | edges |
84 
85  Use the functions table_get_value() to retrieve field data as show
86  in the following example. To see a list of table identifiers
87  consider the function table_get_row_ids(), table_get_column_ids(),
88  or module table_dump(). See datatypes/table.scad for other
89  available table functions. For a general introduction to this
90  topic, see Wikipedia on [Polyhedron].
91 
92 
93  \b Example
94  \code{.C}
95  include <omdl-base.scad>;
96  include <units/coordinate.scad>;
97  include <tools/polytope.scad>;
98  include <database/geometry/polyhedra/platonic.scad>;
99 
100  tc = dtc_polyhedra_platonic;
101  tr = dtr_polyhedra_platonic;
102 
103  id = "dodecahedron";
104 
105  pv = table_get_value(tr, tc, id, "c");
106  pf = table_get_value(tr, tc, id, "f");
107 
108  sv = coordinate_scale3d_csc(pv, 100);
109 
110  polytope_number(sv, pf, to=[0,0,5]);
111  polytope_frame(sv, pf) {circle(r=2); color("grey") sphere(r=4);}
112  polyhedron(sv, pf);
113  \endcode
114 
115  \b Autotests
116 
117  \amu_scope scope (index=1)
118  \amu_if ( -n ${scope} )
119  { \include ${scope}.log }
120  else
121  { \note Database verification results not included. To test and
122  include results, remove \c db_autotest from \c scopes_exclude
123  in library makefile. For more information see \ref lb. }
124  endif
125 
126  [Polyhedron]: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polyhedron
127 
128  @{
129 *******************************************************************************/

21508 BEGIN_SCOPE db;
21509 BEGIN_SCOPE autotest;
21510  BEGIN_OPENSCAD;
21511  include <omdl-base.scad>;
21512  include <units/coordinate.scad>;
21513  include <tools/polytope.scad>;
21514  include <database/geometry/polyhedra/polyhedra_all.scad>;
21515 
21516  coordinates_positive_angles = false;
21517 
21518  tc = dtc_polyhedra_polyhedra_all;
21519  tr = dtr_polyhedra_polyhedra_all;
21520 
21521  log_echo("checking table: ");
21522  log_echo("colums = dtc_polyhedra_polyhedra_all");
21523  log_echo(" rows = dtr_polyhedra_polyhedra_all");
21524  table_check (tr, tc, verbose=true);
21525 
21526  echo();
21527  log_echo("confirming calculations stored in table:");
21528  log_echo(" (1) spherical with converted cartesian coordinates:");
21529  log_echo(" (2) edge list from faces definition:");
21530 
21531  for ( id = table_get_row_ids( tr ) )
21532  {
21533  c = table_get_value(tr, tc, id, "c");
21534  s = table_get_value(tr, tc, id, "s");
21535  f = table_get_value(tr, tc, id, "f");
21536  e = table_get_value(tr, tc, id, "e");
21537 
21538  // convert stored spherical and compare with cartesian coordinates.
21539  for( i = [0 : len(c)-1] )
21540  {
21541  cc = coordinate(s[i], from="s");
21542 
21543  if ( !almost_eq_nv(c[i], cc) )
21544  {
21545  cs = coordinate(c[i], to="s");
21546 
21547  n = table_get_value(tr, tc, id, "n");
21548  o = table_get_value(tr, tc, id, "o");
21549  g = table_get_value(tr, tc, id, "g");
21550  d = table_get_value(tr, tc, id, "d");
21551 
21552  log_warn("coordinate mismatch");
21553  log_info(str("id=", id,", n=", n, ", o=", o, ", g=", g, ", d=", d));
21554  echo(i=i, dt_c=c[i], c_c=cc, dt_s=s[i], c_s=cs);
21555  }
21556  }
21557 
21558  // re-create sorted edge list and compare with stored.
21559  ce = sort_q2(polytope_faces2edges(f), d=1);
21560 
21561  if ( e != ce )
21562  {
21563  se = sort_q2(e, d=1);
21564  if ( se == ce )
21565  {
21566  log_info(str("edge-list not sorted: id=", id));
21567  }
21568  else
21569  {
21570  n = table_get_value(tr, tc, id, "n");
21571  o = table_get_value(tr, tc, id, "o");
21572  g = table_get_value(tr, tc, id, "g");
21573  d = table_get_value(tr, tc, id, "d");
21574
